        <mxCell id="note1" value="LUCIDCHART_DIAGRAMS.md is not draw.io format — it uses Mermaid inside Markdown (for Lucidchart “Import → Mermaid” or GitHub preview).&#xa;&#xa;This file (.drawio) is for diagrams.net / draw.io: open with File → Open from Device, or drag onto app.diagrams.net.&#xa;&#xa;Page “1 — Component architecture” mirrors Diagram 1 from the markdown.&#xa;Diagrams 2–9 in the .md file are sequence / flow Mermaid blocks; paste them into draw.io via Arrange → Insert → Advanced → Mermaid, or keep maintaining them in LUCIDCHART_DIAGRAMS.md." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;fillColor=#fffde7;strokeColor=#f9a825;fontSize=12;" vertex="1" parent="1r">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="40" width="1000" height="200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="note2" value="RFCs / specs (see ARCHITECTURE.md §1a): RFC 6749, 6750, 7636, 7662, 8693, 7009, 7517, 7519, 7591; JSON-RPC 2.0; OIDC Core + CIBA; MCP 2024-11-05." style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingLeft=10;spacingTop=6;fillColor=#e3f2fd;strokeColor=#1565c0;fontSize=11;" vertex="1" parent="1r">
